-- Turkey’s Dogus Holding Seeks $250 Million Three-Year Term Loan
-- B y   L o u i s e   M e e s o n
-- 2012-07-04T15:34:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/turkey-s-dogus-holding-seeks-250-million-three-year-term-loan.html
Dogus Holding AS, the Turkish company
with interests in banking, construction and tourism, is seeking
a $250 million loan, according to a statement on the company’s
 website .  The three-year multicurrency facility will be used for
general corporate purposes and to support trade finance
requirements of subsidiaries, the Istanbul-based company said.  Syndication of the loan, which is being arranged by Banc of
America Securities Ltd. and Citigroup Inc, started yesterday,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Louise Meeson in London at 
